Multi Language Support:

This can be developed using the config driven based, where the data(config) comes from backend whenever the language changes based on it we can render it on the frontend.

<select value={lang} onChange={(e) => setLang(e.target.value)}>
    <option value="en">English</option>
    <option value="hi">Hindi</option>
    <option value="sp">Spanish</option>
    <option value="ru">Russian</option>
</select>

https://github.com/namastedev/namaste-frontend-system-design/blob/master/LLD/app/src/utils/langConstant.js
